==English==

===Adjective===
'''[[high]]-[[maintenance]]'''
#Describes a system which requires a high degree of [[maintenance]] to ensure proper functioning and without which it is likely to break down.
#Figuratively, describes a person who requires a lot of attention.
#:''Rod has this incredibly high-maintenance girlfriend.  If he doesn't tell her, like, every five minutes that he loves her, she tends to break down into hysterical depressive weepy fits.''

===Antonyms===
*[[low-maintenance]]

